4mMURDER24m(1)                        User Commands                       4mMURDER24m(1)

1mNAME0m
       1mmurder 22m- smart Linux process killer

       Inspired by Evan Hahn's murder script

1mSYNOPSIS0m
       murder [-hfqonc] PID|NAME|:PORT

1mOPTIONS0m
       1m-h, --help0m
              Show help message

       1m-f, --force0m
              Kill without confirmation

       1m-q, --quiet0m
              Quiet mode (minimal output)

       1m-o, --one0m
              Kill only the specified process, not the entire tree

       1m-c, --name-only0m
              Search by process name only (not full command line)

       1m-n, --dry-run0m
              Show what would be killed without actually killing

1mNOTES0m
       By  default,  1mmurder 22mkills the process and all its descendants. To kill
       only the specified process, use 1m-o 22mor 1m--one0m

       In NAME mode, 1mmurder 22msearches for NAME as a substring in the full  com-
       mand  line  (e.g.,  4mpython24m  matches  both  4m/usr/bin/python324m  and 4mpython0m
       4mscript.py24m).  To  search  only  in  the  executable  name,  use  1m-c   22mor
       1m--name-only0m

1mARGUMENTS0m
       1mPID    22mProcess ID to kill (e.g., 1234)

       1mNAME   22mProcess name to kill (e.g., python, emacs, firefox)

       1m:PORT  22mPort number to kill process on (e.g., :3000)

1mEXAMPLES0m
       1mmurder 12340m
              Kill process with PID 1234

       1mmurder -f ruby0m
              Kill all ruby processes without asking

       1mmurder -q :30000m
              Kill process on port 3000 quietly

       1mmurder -fq python0m
              Kill python processes without asking and quietly

       1mmurder -nf firefox0m
              Show what would be killed (search by full command)

       1mmurder -nfc firefox0m
              Show what would be killed (search by name only)

       1mmurder -nfq firefox0m
              Show what would be killed with minimal output

1mREQUIREMENTS0m
       1mPerl 5.005 or higher0m
              Usually pre-installed on any Linux system

       1mps     22mStandard Unix tool (pre-installed)

       1mlsof 22mor 1mss0m
              Optional, required only for port killing mode (:PORT)

1mSEE ALSO0m
       kill(1), pkill(1), lsof(8), ss(8)

murder                           February 2026                       4mMURDER24m(1)
